    <stitle>CF 500, CF 600 Steering - Power Steering - Power Steering Description and Operation</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="2">
        <title>Power Steering Description and Operation</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Pump Identification</title>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>Always use the ID code when ordering service parts.</para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <para>The pump identification code is located on a tag attached to the power steering pump.</para>
            <figure id="f1102001" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/n0034578.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Model Code</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">For manufacturing purposes only</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Day of the month</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Shift</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Month</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Year</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Steering Gear Identification</title>
            <para>The steering gear specification number and date code are stamped on a machined surface opposite the
                input shaft of every TAS steering gear. An example date code would be 012-99; this means the gear was
                built on the 12th day of 1999.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1102002" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/n0034579.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="352px"/>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Specification number</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Build date code</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
